1) User Must have installed Python 3 version in his machine

2) create a folder and inside it follow given steps and create VENV in the system
    0)pip install virtualenv
    1)py -m venv project-name
    2)pip install -r [location]\\requirements.txt
    3)virtualenv env [.\env\Scripts\activate.bat]

3) activate the VENV and install all dependencies from requirements.txt file
    pip install -r requirements.txt

4) come inside project folder which is 'Demo' in terminal
    run in terminal > py manage.py runserver

5) set the below details in POSTMAN or and REST tool and hit the URLs in the given format
Don't Change the URL format
Don't Change the HEADER format
Don't Change the BODY format
You can change x and y values only

HEADER
======
content_type="application/json"

URLs
====
http://127.0.0.1:8000/home/add/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/home/sub/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/home/mul/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/home/div/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/home/pow/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/home/fact/

REQUEST BODY
============
JSON_BODY = {
    "x": 5,
    "y": 5
}
'''
